# LICENSE

**NanoFlowSIM Ecosystem**
Copyright (c) 2026 NanoFlowSIM

This project is a multi-layered open-source ecosystem. Different components are covered by different licenses to maximize openness while ensuring that improvements are shared back with the community.

## 1. Hardware Designs
**Applies to:** `/hardware`, `/mechanical`, `/consumables` directories (Schematics, PCB layouts, CAD models, BOMs).

**License:** **CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Weakly Reciprocal (CERN-OHL-W)**

> This license ensures that the hardware designs remain open. You can manufacture and sell hardware based on these designs, but if you modify the design files themselves, you must share those modifications under the same license.

*The full text of the CERN-OHL-W v2 license is included at the bottom of this file.*

## 2. Software & Firmware
**Applies to:** `/core`, `/software`, `/firmware` directories (Source code, binaries, scripts).

**License:** **GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0)**

> This license ensures that the software remains free. If you distribute the software (modified or unmodified), you must also provide the source code under the same license.

*Full license text available at: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt*

## 3. Documentation & Data
**Applies to:** `/docs`, `/protocol`, `/production` directories (Guides, specifications, white papers, datasheets).

**License:** **Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0)**

> This license allows you to share and adapt the documentation, even commercially, as long as you credit the original authors and distribute your contributions under the same license.

*Full license text available at: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/*

